In this entity, we have the ID field (`id`) which is automatically generated by MongoDB. We also have the composite ID and description fields, along with the filtered data (`field1` and `field2`), and the timestamp field (`timestamp`) which represents the date and time when the data was fetched and stored in MongoDB.

You can then create a `DataRepository` interface that extends `ReactiveMongoRepository<Data, String>` to handle CRUD operations on this entity:
