Here's an example implementation of a `save` method and a `load` method in PHP for serializing and deserializing an object to and from a flat file:
```php
class Entity {
  private $data;

  public function __construct($data) {
    $this->data = $data;
  }

  public function save() {
    $serializedData = serialize($this->data);
    file_put_contents('entity.dat', $serializedData);
  }

  public function load() {
    $serializedData = file_get_contents('entity.dat');
    $this->data = unserialize($serializedData);
  }
}
```
This implementation uses the `serialize` and `unserialize` functions to convert the data to and from a string representation that can be written to disk using the `file_put_contents` and `file_get_contents` functions.

