The `waitUntil()` method is called to ensure that the service worker does not terminate before the notification is displayed. This method takes a promise as its argument and waits for the promise to resolve or reject before terminating the service worker.

Note that the code in `service-worker.js` may need to be customized to fit the specific requirements of your web application or PWA. For example, you may need to handle different types of notifications or display them differently to the user.

