 app\_hasher:
 # the service ID of your custom hasher (the FQCN using the default services.yaml)
 id:
[END CHUNK 2/3]
Reply with OK: [CHUNK x/TOTAL], don't reply anything else, don't explain the text!

To enhance the data grid function in `ObjectRelationalHybrid` class to allow users to set up a custom query, we can add a new function called `customQuery()` that takes a query string as input and returns an array of records that match the query. Here is the updated function:
```php
public function customQuery($query) {
    $db = $this->getDBHandle();
    $result = $db->query($query);
    $records = array();
    while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
        $record = new stdClass();
        foreach ($row as $key => $value) {
            $record->$key = $value;
        }
        $records[] = $record;
    }
    return $records;
}
```
This function uses the `getDBHandle()` function to get a handle to the database and then executes the custom query using the `query()` function. It then retrieves the result set using the `fetch_assoc()` function and constructs an array of records that match the query.

We can then modify the `getDataGrid()` function to accept an optional query string that will be used to retrieve the data. Here is the updated function:
```php
public function getDataGrid($query = null) {
    if (!$this->tableName) {
        return false;
    }

    $records = array();
    if ($query) {
        // Use custom query
        $records = $this->customQuery($query);
    } else {
        // Use default query
        $db = $this->getDBHandle();
        $result = $db->query("SELECT * FROM " . $this->tableName);
        while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
            $record = new stdClass();
            foreach ($row as $key => $value) {
                $record->$key = $value;
            }
            $records[] = $record;
        }
    }

    // Generate HTML table
    $html = '<table><thead><tr>';
    foreach ($this->fieldDefs as $field => $type) {
        $html .= '<th>' . $field . '</th>';
    }
    $html .= '<th>Actions</th></tr></thead><tbody>';
    foreach ($records as $record) {
        $html .= '<tr>';
        foreach ($this->fieldDefs as $field => $type) {
            $html .= '<td>' . $record->$field . '</td>';
        }
